The story behind some of Princess Diana's most unforgettable 
looks, told through the couture dresses that went to auction in 
the biggest ever UK sale of her clothes.

With exclusive access to Kerry Taylor Auctions, the programme 
examines how Diana's style evolved, the statement that was made 
by each outfit choice and why these particular dresses were key 
throughout her time in the spotlight.

Unseen archive footage and interviews with the style insiders 
who knew her best reveal what motivated Diana's fashion decisions.

From the 25-foot train of her wedding gown that was longer than 
any other royal train, to the off-shoulder velvet gown she wore 
when she famously danced with John Travolta, and the striking 
halter neck black dress that was captured by Mario Testino, 
viewers get an insight into how the princess used her clothes 
to express her individuality.

The film shows Diana's growth in confidence and how she came to 
understand that her clothes could speak volumes.

She began to know exactly how to dress for the occasion and could 
always be relied upon to give the public the picture they wanted, 
always walking down the red carpet as the epitome of glamour.
